<span id="freeTextContainer6466211649188181192">3-1/2 Stars<br/><br/>In The Light of the Garden, 31-year-old Charity returns to her grandfather’s home upon learning of his passing. This is a place full of fond childhood memories from Charity’s summers spent there with her grandparents. Upon returning as an adult, many secrets are discovered. <br/><br/>This a book about forgiveness and loss. What makes it intriguing is that the author adds a bit of magic to the storyline. There is something mysterious about the willow tree and a “secret ingredient” Grandpa left f</span>
  <span id="freeText6466211649188181192" style="display:none">3-1/2 Stars<br /><br />In The Light of the Garden, 31-year-old Charity returns to her grandfather’s home upon learning of his passing. This is a place full of fond childhood memories from Charity’s summers spent there with her grandparents. Upon returning as an adult, many secrets are discovered. <br /><br />This a book about forgiveness and loss. What makes it intriguing is that the author adds a bit of magic to the storyline. There is something mysterious about the willow tree and a “secret ingredient” Grandpa left for Charity to use in her pottery making. Family drama unfolds as we learn the answers to these mysteries. </span>
