  <span id="freeText13913054907352829994" style="display:none">"In the Light of the Garden" is a gorgeous, lyrical journey. Heather Burch creates a cast of characters full of quirks and flaws that draw you in and make you root for them all to have a happy ending. The weeping willow reminds me of the forgiveness and grace we all crave and don't think we deserve. It also asks the question, "What is a family?" A family is not only made up of blood relatives but the people we invite into our lives. Bravo, Heather for another great book!</span>
